"{    \"translations\": [        {            \"english_version\": \"The Federal Reserve decided to keep the interest rate the same. They plan to lower rates three times this year because the economy is slowing down. The chairman, Jerome Powell, is happy that inflation is going down. But he didn't say when the rate cuts will start.\",            \"english_title\": \"Interest Rate Decision\",            \"translated_version\": \"El Federal Reserve decidi\u00f3 mantener la tasa de inter\u00e9s igual. Planea bajar las tasas tres veces este a\u00f1o porque la econom\u00eda se est\u00e1 desacelerando. El presidente, Jerome Powell, est\u00e1 contento de que la inflaci\u00f3n est\u00e9 bajando. Pero no dijo cu\u00e1ndo comenzar\u00e1n los recortes de tasas.\",            \"translated_title\": \"Decisi\u00f3n sobre la Tasa de Inter\u00e9s\"        },        {            \"english_version\": \"Reddit set the price of its shares at $34 before listing on the stock market. This values the company at about $6.4 billion. They will raise $748 million through the share sale. This is good news as there haven't been many exciting public offerings recently.\",            \"english_title\": \"Reddit Share Price\",            \"translated_version\": \"Reddit fij\u00f3 el precio de sus acciones en $34 antes de cotizar en el mercado de valores. Esto valora a la empresa en aproximadamente $6.4 mil millones. Recaudar\u00e1n $748 millones a trav\u00e9s de la venta de acciones. Esta es una buena noticia ya que no ha habido muchas ofertas p\u00fablicas emocionantes recientemente.\",            \"translated_title\": \"Precio de las Acciones de Reddit\"        },        {            \"english_version\": \"The US government will give $8.5 billion to Intel and provide $11 billion in loans. This is to help Intel make more advanced computer chips. They also hope to get $25 billion in tax breaks to compete with other chipmakers. The CHIPS act aims to boost the semiconductor industry in the US.\",            \"english_title\": \"US Support for Intel\",            \"translated_version\": \"El gobierno de EE. UU. dar\u00e1 $8.5 mil millones a Intel y proporcionar\u00e1 $11 mil millones en pr\u00e9stamos. Esto es para ayudar a Intel a fabricar chips de computadora m\u00e1s avanzados. Tambi\u00e9n esperan obtener $25 mil millones en exenciones fiscales para competir con otros fabricantes de chips. La ley CHIPS tiene como objetivo impulsar la industria de semiconductores en EE. UU.\",            \"translated_title\": \"Apoyo de EE. UU. a Intel\"        },        {            \"english_version\": \"Leo Varadkar unexpectedly resigned as Ireland's prime minister. He first took office in 2017 and became the youngest prime minister. He resigned for personal and political reasons. Ireland will have a general election by 2025.\",            \"english_title\": \"Resignation of Leo Varadkar\",            \"translated_version\": \"Leo Varadkar renunci\u00f3 inesperadamente como primer ministro de Irlanda. Tom\u00f3 el cargo por primera vez en 2017 y se convirti\u00f3 en el primer ministro m\u00e1s joven. Renunci\u00f3 por razones personales y pol\u00edticas. Irlanda tendr\u00e1 una elecci\u00f3n general para 2025.\",            \"translated_title\": \"Renuncia de Leo Varadkar\"        },        {            \"english_version\": \"Vietnam's president, Vo Van Thuong, resigned after a year in office due to violations. This has affected the reputation of the Communist Party. Canada decided not to approve new weapons-export permits to Israel because of the situation in Gaza.\",            \"english_title\": \"Resignation in Vietnam and Canada's Decision\",            \"translated_version\": \"El presidente de Vietnam, Vo Van Thuong, renunci\u00f3 despu\u00e9s de un a\u00f1o en el cargo debido a violaciones. Esto ha afectado la reputaci\u00f3n del Partido Comunista. Canad\u00e1 decidi\u00f3 no aprobar nuevos permisos de exportaci\u00f3n de armas a Israel debido a la situaci\u00f3n en Gaza.\",            \"translated_title\": \"Renuncia en Vietnam y Decisi\u00f3n de Canad\u00e1\"        }    ]}"